description: Dimensions: L 112.5mm; We 34.3; Wm 32.8; min W. 22.9; Bm 32.5; Blp 6; DS 71.5 (?+),Typology: central rib with rounded crest and steep walls in cross section, but leading to flatten towards tip; m. top flat to slightly outsloped; body angles mainly a little rounded,Manufacture: broken surfaces on m. top suggest two bases of runners, above faces; cg. flashes quite broad, crests flattened by hammer, but only fully removed along lower blade; hints of bl. tip hollows but flanking ridges largely levelled off by anc. grinding - horiz. scmks.; crinoline bl. prob. due to expansion - assoc. bevel and hammer ripples on rev. where p. visible, as well as numerous grmks. approx. horiz. which go beneath accretion.,Condition: probably intact edge prior to minimal patina flaking and modern interference.,Attached Material: when submitted calcareous soil adhered to exterior and base of socket; traces of fawn soil and soil bump in s. end - not core like.

surface: dark brown to gold patina; subst. areas with variable white green - bright green textured sur.
associations: 1a. Hoard
description: Dimension: L 124.2mm; We 65.1; Wm 41.8; Bm 44.1; Blp 11.8; DS 86,Typology: lower m-m pronounced rib; narrow rect. flat s. end,Manufacture: sl. anomalous bulge on rev. face of m-m apparently slight dislocation between two mould valves; cg. fl. - parts rounded crested, ? untrimmed, others flattened with irreg. lipping; hole in body face with rounded edges - cg. flaw; stump of fairly thick cg. fl. round s.m. - part broken sur., part hammered with assoc. lipping - int. & ext.; poor metal flaw above hole - no. of fissures; s. core misplaced - off centre; small half-moon depressions in one face seem like anc. pmks.,Attached Material: white and light brown deposits
remarks: Labels/Markings: white ink "3652/12",Archive: PIF; AFI,PRBAF: DF(C); SI,Ext:CI,Rec.: SN. Oct. 79,Source: MV,Old Cards: 1

surface: Gross to emerald green patina, small dull gold patch; patina flakes at edges; intense pocking to light green + dull brown around m.
associations: 1b. Hoard
description: Dimensions: EL 80.5mm; max EW bl 20.5mm; Ws (below blade) 9.7mm; W across lps. 14.9mm; EWm 17.2mm; EBm 17.8mm; min Blp 2mm; Ds 76,Typology: bl. prob. orig. with flame-shape; loz. midrib becomes more rounded for socket but with very slight crest rib, and expands (sl. convexity to the expansion) at m. to oval; loop plates not part. regular, both with construction in lower part,Manufacture: variable stump of cg. fl. - thin - along s. sides, totally removed on lps. & prob. at m; some suggestions of hammer ripples on s.; forging poss. created crest ribs also odd off-centre sl. rib on reverse face; small hole on reverse side below lp. - probably cg. flaw, rounded edges.,Condition: series of str. along bl. + midrib, others transverse on s. and midrib - could be anx.; other impressions look like vice grip marks and file ripples; lead like substance at main break - solder?,Attached Material: very chalky buff soil coat inside s. + loops
remarks: Label/Markings: White ink: "2.44/2",Archive PIF; AFI,PRBAF: DF (C); SI,Ext. CI,Rec: SN Oct. 79,Source: MV

surface: Mainly varied green dry surface, some textured, overlying black-green patina, exposed in patches.
associations: 1a. Hoard
description: Dimensions: L 107mm; We 65.2; Wm 39; Bm 42.9; min Blp 7.7; DS 72.3,Typology: spasmodic flattening of upper m-m, but largely biconical; 3 rib motif - some bowed if not evenly spaced - disappear before joining lower m-m; rounded body angles; lp. little asymm.; narrow rect. s. end.,Manufacture: few hmks. discernible on lower bl. face, assoc. with bulge in sides just above expanded bl. e., but no bl. tip hollows; thin cg. fl. stump along much of sides, little wavy and asym.; flattening of thick cg. fl. at m. causing some lipping - inside and out.,Condition: edge intact, fairly sharp - 2 small nicks prob. mod. interference,Attached Material: areas with chalky accretion, also mid-brown soil traces.

surface: Dull browny-green dry sur.; little brighter green tex. patches; some smooth grey-brown to gold surface.
associations: 1a. Hoard
description: Dimensions: L 133.8mm; We 52.2; Wm 41.2; Bm 39.8; Blp. 9; DS 91; BW.s end approx. 8mm,Typology: sl. bowed faces, more convex sides, body angles crisp & emphasised by sl. ribs for much of length; bulb on face only between two m-ms - little off axis - not obviously dec.; narrow but flat ended bl. e. as cast.,Manufacture: cg. fl. thin - much round crested, some hmg. tending to lip over to one side only; battered stump only along bl. e.; thin upstanding cg. fl. for part of m. broadens to two lenticular stumps of jets above faces - much flat-topped, some lpg. but smooth finish might indicate e. grinding as well as hmg.; lpg int. & ext.; irreg. & jagged ridge vert. down int. s. face, close to corner, from m. for short distance; other crude projections inside s.; some dimpled sur. - prob. as cast.,Condition: unfinished, undamaged,Attached Material: patches of chalky buff accretion; orangey-brown soil spots on outside, plus fair coating inside socket - poss. more orange - not partic. sandy
remarks: Labels/Markings: black print marking: '3652/7',Archive: PIF; AFI,PRBAF: DF(C); SI,Ext: CI,Rec.: SN Oct. 79,Source: MV,Old Card: 1

site: England,Sussex,Sompting,Hill Barn Nurseries,Discovered by a mechanical excavator at a point 300 feet north-east of Hill Barn, Sompting and 1,500 feet south-west of the south-west edge of Lancing Ring (TQ 176062), October 1846. Five feet deep in an accumulation of brown clayey mould.
associations: Leeds Class B2 bronze cauldron,Hoard
description: Rough casting with collar. A pair of nearly parallel raised lines ending in a pellet decorate each edge of the two faces. Each pair of lines is slightly curved, perhaps in imitation of wings. On one face, between the two pairs of lines, is a circle motif. Iron stain on one face.
publications: Ant. Journ. XXVIII (1948), pp. 157-163 and Plate XX, 6.,Sussex N. & Queries Vol. 12, 1, pp. 9-11.
remarks: From the same mould as No. 3652/5

surface: Little browny gold smooth sur., mainly green sur., dry & textured; few purply patches
associations: 1a. Hoard
description: Dimension: L 107.3mm; We 46; W 34.9; Bm 35.6; Blp 4.8; DS 82.5,Typology: SOMPTING MODEL 2: second m-m on sides disappear on faces; three ribs outline edges of faces, from below upper m-m for 2.3 of L.; thin ribs, one along body angle, irreg. spacing, more bowed towards centre of axe; 3 still terminate in pellets - not quite level; large ring between on one face; s. end v. narrow rect.,Manufacture: thin cg. fl. down most of sides - central stretch on rev. removed fully and bordering parts flattened; cg. fl. along bl. e. flattened with lipping one side - but bl. otherwise unworked and blunt; part of narrow crest to m-m flattened causing int. lipping; some dimpling of sur. - prob. moulding marks.,Condition: two broad broken surfaces at m., stumps of jets.,Attached Material: chalky - light brown accretion and soil adhering
remarks: Labels/Markings: black print marking: '3652/6',Archive: PIF; AFI,PRBAF: DF(C); SI,Ext.: CI,Rec.: SN Oct. 79,Source: MV,Old Card: 1

surface: Dull browny green dry sur., with odd patches of gold; ruddy brown areas at m. - ?iron-stained
associations: 1a. Hoard
description: Dimensions: L 106.1mm; We 45.8; Wm 35.1; Bm 34.5; Blp 4.7; DS 79.5,Typology: SOMPTING MODEL 2; lower m-m v. slight, disappears intermittently; v. narrow rect. s. end; bl. e. flat-ended.,Manufacture: cg. fl. v. thin down sides, little thicker at bl. e. - much round crested & undulating, some flattened with assoc. lpg.; well smoothed inside lp.; quite thin broken e. of cg. fl. round m. seems consistently to face inwards, thus narrow flatt. top of m. poss. cast? certainly a prom. lip at one point suggests some hmg. inwards, curling down towards s.; broken ribs - miscast - also pres. terminal pellets and central motif - missing on rev.; depressions in m. top with round top - mould cavity not filled; cast dimpled sur. in parts.,Condition: unfinished - no edge preparation.,Attached Material: small patches of chalky-buff accretion; spot of orange-brown soil matrix inside s., plus another prob. lighter in colour at s. end.
remarks: Labels/Markings: black print marking "3652/5",Archive: PIF; AFI,PRBAF: DF(C); SI,Ext.: CI,Rec. SN Oct. 79,Source: MV

publications: Ant. Journ. XXVIII (1948), pp. 157-163 and Plate XX, 4.

surface: Mainly dull green dry uneven or textured sur., patches of brightish gold to dull brown, also some bright green.
associations: 1a. Hoard
description: Dimensions: L 136mm; We 59; Wm 44; Bm 40; Blp 8; DS 109.5,Typology: SOMPTING MODEL I; most of ring-and-pellet diffuse, and exact form not discernible; socket-end-slit.,Manufacture: thin cg. fl. for most of sides into much rounded untrimmed crest, parts flattened, or removed at m. or rev. side; becomes v. broad at bl. e., where traces of broken sur. mainly observed by flattened sur. with assoc. lipping; about 3.4 of m. has cg. fl. rem. - some quite thick with broken or flat sur., but also thin jagged untrimmed fl. bent inwards; part of m. incomplete - cavity not fitted; step in line of lower m-m on sides suggest values not matched; short wavy ridge on bl. adj. to e. - cg. flaws - as also broken ribs etc.; few hmks. on ext. face of upper m-m.,Condition: unfinished,Attached Material: frags. of pale orange sandy matrix att. to interior of socket - prob. core remts.; chalky buff and rich ochreous brown deposits on outside, also orange-brown soil traces.
remarks: Archive: PIF; AFI,PRBAF: DF(C); SI,Ext.: CI,Rec.: SN Oct. 79,Source: MV,Old Card: 1

site: England,Sussex (West),Sompting,Hill Barn Nursuries,No. 3,Old B.A.C. card for this axe labelled 3652/3 presumably incorrectly swapped - in fact correlate's with Corwen's numbering (a).
surface: Raised dull to bright green sur., with patches dull gold, textured with shallow craters
associations: 1a. Hoard
description: Dimensions: L 134.3mm; We 60.3; Wm 44.9; Bm 41.5; Blp 8.3; DS 100.5,Typology: Virt. flat faces with 4 ribs terminating in poss. pellets; ribs not entirely regular - some bowing and uneven spacing; pellets form diag. line - same on both faces; above, and between ribs, spasmodic traces of double-ring-and-dot motif; body sides bowed in sec.; slit s. end,Manufacture: change in level of m-m as sides suggest not perfectly matching valves; cg. fl. medium thin for much of sides - parts rounded instead as cast, others flattened with assoc. lipping; cg. fl. become v. broad at bl. e. with undulating flat top - post broken, part cut sur. - only a little lipping from hammering; stump of cg. fl. round most of m. top, v. little int. and ext. lipping; cg. fl. inside lp.; short tib at bl. e. adj. to cg. fl. cg.-flaw, as also occ. metal pimples and depressions in body and breaks in ribs; short stretch of thin cg-flaw inside s.,Condition: unfinished,Attached Material: chalky buff accretion round part of m.; occ. small trace of light brown soil, also a small patch of iron-stained accretia.
remarks: Labels/Markings: black  print marking "3652/2",Archive: PIF; AFI,PRBAF: DF(C); SI,Ext.: CI,Rec.: SN Oct. 79,Source: MV,Old Card: 1

site: England,Sussex (West),Sompting,Hill Barn Nursuries,No. 2,Old B.A.C. card for this axes labelled 3652/2 presumably incorrectly swapped - or more likely derived from Curwen's slightly different numbering (a)
surface: Mainly dry dull green surface, partly textured: little smooth green-brown surface.
associations: 1a. Hoard
description: Dimensions: L 135.5; We 59.2; Wm 43.5; Bm 40.5; Blp 5; DS 113,Typology: v. sl. 2nd m-m with 4 ribs descending, thin sometimes broken and a little irregularly spaced terminate in sloped line of pellets - same diagonal on either face; roundels between ribs above pellets - some with hints of pellets within; right most ribs follow body angles - otherwise rounded; slit s. end,Manufacture: sl. dislocation in m-m at valve junction; hollow in one face - cg. flaw, as also breaks in some ribs; cg. fl. stumps thin for much of sides, but v. thick along bl. e. - flattened crests look cut; v. thin flash projecting inside lp.; moulding flaw at mouth on rev. side - flattening of m-m top associated with marked internal lipping round part of mouth; small length of thin sharp cg. fl. inside s.l. remains of protruberance in one upper m-m.,Condition: unfinished, undamaged.,Attached Material: v. pale buff accretion/soil and light brown soil in small patches.
remarks: Label/Markings: black print marking: 3652/3,Archive: PIF; AFI,PRBAF: DF(C); SI,Ext.: CI,Rec.: SN Oct. 79,Source: MV,Old Card: 1

site: England,Sussex,Sompting,Hill Barn Nurseries,Discovered by a mechanical excavator at a point 300 feet north-east of Hill Barn, Sompting and 1,500 feet south-west of the south-west edge of Lancing Ring (TQ 176062), October, 1946. Five feet deep in an accumulation of brown clayey mould.
associations: Leeds Class B2 cauldron.,Hoard
description: Rough casting with horizontal raised band below a collar and four vertical ribs ending in pellets on two sides; between each rib there is a dot in the centre of two concentric circles. Most of collar missing through imperfect casting. Incrustation of iron rust on one face.
publications: Ant. Journ. XXVIII (1948), pp. 157-163 and Plate XX, 1.,Sussex N. & Q., Vol. 12, 1, pp. 9-11

surface: Varied green to dull brown dimple-textured sur.
associations: 1a. Hoard
description: Dimensions: L 120.3; We 58.9; Wstlp 44.9; Blp 8.2; Bm 32.5; DS 94.5,Typology: 4 ribs terminate in pellets forming sl. oblique line - sim. diag. on either face; hints of ring-snd-pellet motifs between rib ends; SOMPTING MODEL I; slit s. end,Manufacture: m. more or less as-cast - insufficient metal to fill mould; some hmks on top, poss. with assoc. int. lipping; narrow cg. fl. on sides becomes v. broad at e. - mostly flattened with assoc. lipping; sl. ridge at top of int. side on line of valve junction; short wavy rib on bl. adj. to e. - cg. flaw, as also broken ribs and acc. sur. irreg.; prong of cg. fl. inside loop; lentoid pmks on sides low down - anc.,Condition: unfinished,Attached Material: fairly thick deposit on much of rev. face - dark brown and orange, iron-rich; smaller scattered deposites of chalky accretion; small traces of light brown soil.
remarks: Label: black ink printed marking: '3652' changed from 3652/3,Archive: PIF; AFI,PRBAF: DF(C); SI,Ext.: CI,Rec.: SN Oct. 79,Source: MV

surface: Where intact, a dull yellow-brown smooth by dry surface with small cracks; yello-white similar surface inside perforation; chipped parts of surface glassy vermillion.
associations: 1b. Hoard
description: Dimensions: max E. d. 28.2mm; bore of perforation 2.5; t (max) 15.5; max d. at entrance to perforation 3.5,Typology: biconic profile with sub-tri shape, each face tending to have three facets,Manufacture: perforation almost cylindrical - very slight widening at ends, perhaps a little skew.,Condition: 2 edges virtually intact - apex between little damaged, as also third edge and bordering apexes - all suffering from flaking of adjacent faces.
remarks: Label/Markings: white ink: 'L44/4',PIF; AFI; DF(C); SI; CI; Rec. SN Oct. 79; Source: MV

surface: Some smooth dull green patina; most covered in tex. lighter or brighter green surface and light green spots of corr.
description: Dimensions: min. E. intact d. 210; max. E. d. 230; T cone 04-0.7mm; T Range 0.5-0.9; EH boss 100,Typology: present tendency to ell-shape not nec. orig.; boss faces, where not crumpled, gently concave; small out turn at crest consistent on all projections, suggests bead-moulding - one even has convex profile surviving; rib moulding emphasising top of step and rim of fg.; latter with semi-circ. section orig.; base of step prob. orig. an obtuse angle - fairly crisp, but not extremely; outer fg. may have been sl. sloped orig.,Manufacture: tendency to sl. thinner sheet for cone than for surround.,Condition: almost half of outer fg. lost; most of cone crest also broken away, as well as portion of adjacent cone; one half of piece contorted by number of bends - some quite angular - all assoc.with a dull gold brown colour, and prob. recent dam.; numerous other cracks/fractures, esp. along orig. creases etc.; most edges of fracture reveal purply brown core to metal; all perfs. appear to be dam.,Attached Material: light brown soil traces embedded in areas - more chalky buff inside.
remarks: Labels/Markings: black print marking 3652; stuck-on paper label: 15,PIF(0); AFI; DF(C); SI; CI; Rec. SN Oct. 79; Source: MV; Old Card: 1
